<h2>Track work dependencies</h2>

<p>Dependencies show relationships between work items, helping you understand what your work item relies on and what depends on your work item.</p>

<h3>Viewing dependencies</h3>
<p>To view work dependencies:</p>
<ol>
    <li>Navigate to your work item's detail page</li>
    <li>Go to the <strong>Dependencies</strong> tab</li>
    <li>View dependencies in two sections:
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Dependencies (This work item depends on):</strong> Work items your work item needs</li>
            <li><strong>Dependents (Work items that depend on this):</strong> Work items that need your work item</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
</ol>

<h3>Dependency information</h3>
<p>Each dependency shows:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Related Work Item:</strong> The work item being depended on or depending</li>
    <li><strong>Type:</strong> Type of dependency (e.g., Technical, Data, Resource)</li>
    <li><strong>Description:</strong> Details about the dependency</li>
    <li><strong>Status:</strong> Current state of the dependency</li>
    <li><strong>Criticality:</strong> How important the dependency is</li>
</ul>

<h3>Adding a dependency</h3>
<p>To add a new dependency:</p>
<ol>
    <li>Go to the <strong>Dependencies</strong> tab</li>
    <li>Click <strong>Add Dependency</strong></li>
    <li>Select the dependency direction:
        <ul>
            <li><strong>This work item depends on:</strong> Your work item needs another work item</li>
            <li><strong>Work items that depend on this:</strong> Another work item needs yours</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Fill in the dependency details:
        <ul>
            <li>Related work item</li>
            <li>Dependency type</li>
            <li>Description</li>
            <li>Status</li>
            <li>Criticality</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Click <strong>Create</strong></li>
</ol>

<h3>Dependency types</h3>
<p>Common dependency types include:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Technical:</strong> Technical integration or infrastructure</li>
    <li><strong>Data:</strong> Data sharing or data dependencies</li>
    <li><strong>Resource:</strong> Shared resources or people</li>
    <li><strong>Work Item:</strong> Dependency on a specific work item</li>
    <li><strong>Decision:</strong> Waiting on a decision from another work item</li>
</ul>

<h3>Dependency status</h3>
<p>Track the status of dependencies:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Active:</strong> Dependency is current and relevant</li>
    <li><strong>Resolved:</strong> Dependency has been satisfied</li>
    <li><strong>Blocked:</strong> Dependency is blocking progress</li>
    <li><strong>At Risk:</strong> Dependency may not be met on time</li>
</ul>

<h3>Managing dependencies</h3>
<p>For each dependency, you can:</p>
<ul>
    <li>View full details</li>
    <li>Edit the dependency information</li>
    <li>Update status as the dependency changes</li>
    <li>Add notes or comments</li>
    <li>Link to related risks or issues</li>
</ul>

<h3>Dependency impact</h3>
<p>Understanding dependencies helps you:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Identify blockers early</li>
    <li>Coordinate with other work item teams</li>
    <li>Plan for delays or changes</li>
    <li>Communicate impacts to stakeholders</li>
    <li>Manage risks related to dependencies</li>
</ul>

<h3>Best practices</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Document all significant dependencies</li>
    <li>Keep dependency status up to date</li>
    <li>Regularly review dependencies for changes</li>
    <li>Communicate with dependent work items</li>
    <li>Link dependencies to risks where appropriate</li>
    <li>Resolve or close dependencies when no longer relevant</li>
</ul>

